reviewTitle: Perfect no-need-for-adult-help craft project for young crafter - colorful and SPARKLY!
reviewDescription: The description and pictures here on Amazon are right on for this craft project. While it is a very simple craft - simply adding these small "jewel" stickers to the unicorns/princesses etc. pictures, it is great because it is entirely open ended. There is no right or wrong way to do it and it is to be done purely at the whim of the little crafter. The pictures are cute, appealing and printed on a thick "paper board" so they feel and look high quality. The jewels are on the small side but that is not necessarily a drawback as they are made to fit within the colored spaces in the pictures. As long as the crafter can manipulate small stickers (made a little easier because the jewels are thicker than normal stickers) and can be trusted not to put small things in their mouths, then there is no need for adult help . All you have to do is ooh and ahh at the results. Definitely geared toward the lower part of the age range. A big hit with my 4 year old granddaughter! She loved the pictures and loved, loved, loved the shiny jewels! The finished pictures can be hung or stood up easel style with the included parts (they might need help with this). A perfect little kit to pick up and store for when you need a special surprise and entertainment for a young crafter and unicorn/princess lover. Again, it's a simple craft, but that is also its strength - they can gain confidence creating a colorful, sparkly craft all by themselves. A simple win in my book for the right crafter!

reviewTitle: Great way to score grandma points and inspire little crafters
reviewDescription: I have two grandkids - a 3 year old girl and a 5 year old boy. They LOVE to do crafts with grandma. I had gotten a set a while back that had gem stickers and dot stickers and the gem ones were a major hit with both kids, not so much the dots. So, I was super excited to find another set that was just the gem stickers. While the 3 year old girl just loves stickers in general and loves the glittery sparkly aspect, the 5 year old boy completely surprised me with these sets. He is very meticulous about trying to match the shapes and colors to the pictures. I’ve tucked this aside until we have an arts and crafts afternoon, but I can already tell it will be a winner! The pictures are super cute and there are some for boys as well as girls. The gemstones are nice and sparkly in a good assortment of shapes and colors. As a bonus, it even has little stands and hangers so they can put their masterpieces in their rooms.
